title: SEC wants to let small investors into big IPOs
text: Wall Street’s top watchdog wants mom-and-pop investors to grab a slice of the next Facebook before it goes public — but critics fret that they’ll fall prey to the next WeWork.

title: Don’t expect Fed Chairman Jerome Powell to play nice with Trump
text: The relationship between Trump and Fed Chairman Jerome “Jay” Powell can best be described as strained — with all the strain coming from the president’s side.

title: Oil rises, supported by trade deal, OPEC cuts
text: Oil prices rose on Thursday, buoyed by a potential breakthrough in the Sino-U.S. trade war and OPEC-led efforts to constrain supply, although trading was quiet as many markets were in holiday mode.

title: 5 charts show how protests in Hong Kong have affected the city's economy and stock market
text: Widespread protests in Hong Kong have lasted for more than six months — with little signs of abating anytime soon.

title: Record online sales give short U.S. holiday shopping season a boost: report
text: U.S. shoppers spent more online than in retail stores during the shortest winter shopping season in the past six years, with online sales hitting a record high, a report by Mastercard Inc. showed.

title: The tech giants dominated the decade. But there’s still time to rein them in | Jay Owens
text: The 2010s will be remembered for a new era in the development of capitalism, one of mind-boggling scale. Apple, Amazon and Microsoft are closing the decade as the world’s first trillion-dollar companies.

title: 'Tis The Season To Remember Buffett's Farewell Gift To His Partners (And Consider Munis)
text: This piece talks about the generous way in which Buffett dissolved his original Partnership, providing all Partners with investment alternatives, a helpful forecast, and specific advice on munis.

title: The FOMOTINA Rally Has Kicked Into High Gear
text: Bulls Run Wild The FOMOTINA Rally (Fear of Missing Out There Is No Alternative) kicked into high gear, with U.S. stocks hitting record closing highs again on Friday and the S&P 500 registering a 1.65% gain, its biggest weekly rise since early September.

title: The Santa Rally and 2020 Expectations
text: Written by: Edward Moya| Oanda Markets officially entered holiday as trading volumes remain very thin and as Wall Street prepares to take the rest of the week off.

title: China says it is in close touch with U.S. on trade deal signing ceremony
text: China says it is in close touch with the United States on a trade deal signing ceremony, after U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday that he and Chinese President Xi Jinping will have a ceremony to sign the recently struck Phase 1 trade deal.

title: Dividend Yields Around The World
text: Looking at the dividend yields of 22 of the world's largest economies, it may come as a surprise to hear that the United States currently has the second-lowest yield at just 1.83%.
